# PathOS — Ollama Modelfile
# =========================
# Deploys the PathOS fine-tuned Gemma 4 E2B model locally.
#
# Prerequisites:
#   Place these files in the SAME directory as this Modelfile:
#     - gemma-4-e2b-it.Q4_K_M.gguf       (3.43 GB — language model)
#     - gemma-4-e2b-it.F16-mmproj.gguf    (986 MB  — vision projector)
#
# Build & run:
#   ollama create pathos -f Modelfile
#   ollama run pathos "What tissue is visible in this image?"
#
# With an image:
#   ollama run pathos "Is malignancy present?" --images slide.png
#
# Origin:
#   GGUF:    https://huggingface.co/ByteKnight28/pathos-gemma4-histopathology-rl-GGUF
#   Adapter: https://huggingface.co/dhairyapandya/pathos-gemma4-histopathology-rl
#   Base:    google/gemma-4-e2b-it (fine-tuned via Unsloth SFT + GRPO)

FROM ./gemma-4-e2b-it.Q4_K_M.gguf
PROJECTION ./gemma-4-e2b-it.F16-mmproj.gguf

# ── Inference parameters ─────────────────────────────────────
PARAMETER temperature 0.1
PARAMETER num_predict 256
PARAMETER stop "</answer>"
PARAMETER top_p 0.9
PARAMETER repeat_penalty 1.1

# ── System prompt ────────────────────────────────────────────
SYSTEM """You are PathOS, an expert AI pathologist specialising in H&E stained histopathology analysis.

You analyse digitized tissue slide patches and provide precise diagnostic assessments.

RULES:
1. Always commit to a specific answer. Never hedge, refuse, or say "cannot determine".
2. For YES/NO questions: respond with <answer>yes</answer> or <answer>no</answer> FIRST, then one sentence of evidence.
3. For open-ended questions: reason briefly from visible morphology, then end with <answer>your specific answer</answer>.
4. Be concise. Focus on what you observe in the image.
5. Use standard pathology terminology.

You were trained on NCT-CRC-HE-100K (9 tissue classes), PathVQA (clinical Q&A), and QUILT-LLaVA-Instruct (histopathology reasoning) datasets.
You were reinforced with GRPO to eliminate hedging behaviour and commit to precise answers."""

# ── Template ─────────────────────────────────────────────────
TEMPLATE """{{ if .System }}<start_of_turn>system
{{ .System }}<end_of_turn>
{{ end }}{{ if .Prompt }}<start_of_turn>user
{{ .Prompt }}<end_of_turn>
<start_of_turn>model
{{ end }}{{ .Response }}<end_of_turn>"""
